Attributes._Description: "If so all detail lines associated with this split have DOS.  Otherwise we will use today's date to determine MOSA associations for PreDs."
"It's possible there is one MOSA record or more than one for the given DOS range.  Either way we need to find out if one of them is COMM and/or DLTA (delta) and which is primary/secondary."

ChildRules.RuleName: Is the DeltaCoverageInd a B or a P?

Attributes._Description: "CRM ID# 50060\015\012\015\01212/22 - Per defect 81272/CC61 we are changing this remark code to 2MM"
"If so this means at least one DLTA entry was found.  Based on the prior logic, this means there is at least one DLTA = S record."

ChildRules.RuleName: Is the DeltaCoverageInd a B or a P?

Attributes._Description: "Yes - CRM ID# 50038\015\012\015\012No - Per defect 80825 (Change Control 58) this indicates there are entries in the MOSA table but none of them are indicated to be primary.  This is a MetaVance data entry error that we are going to flag with a remark code of 2MM.  "

"From CRM 50043 we should assume Delta is primary if COMM is secondary.  To wit:\015\012\015\012System  prepares the claim for adjudication when DLTA is primary (meaning the COMM entry is secondary coverage).\015\012\015\012There are cases, it seems, where there is only one MOSA entry with COMM = S.  I'm not sure this is normal, but we are seeing this with ginned up data from Delta, so I'm putting a catch in here.  Dan 7/10/09."
